@NODE "introduction" "MP3TagEditor / Introduction"

   MP3TagEditor is a program to edit the ID3v1 & ID3v2 tags in MPEG audio files.
   This program has nice MUI based GUI, drag&drop function, etc.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "requirements" "MP3TagEditor / Requirements"

   Software requirements:

     - id3tag.library v5.1 by David Mevius

     - MUI v3.8 by Stefan Stuntz

     - TextEditor.mcc, BetterString.mcc by Allan Odgaard

     - NList.mcc by Gilles Masson

     - openurl.library by Troels Walsted Hansen (optional)

@ENDNODE
@NODE "installation" "MP3TagEditor / Installation"

   Installation: place it whereever you like on your harddisk,
   e.g. Work:Tools/BestProgs/MP3TagEditor ;))))

   Please note that MP3TagEditor uses id3tag.library so download it
   from Aminet (mus/edit) and copy id3tag.library to LIBS:

   From version 2.2 MP3TagEditor uses new Prefs file format so delete
   old one from ENVARC:MUI/MP3TAGEDITOR.1.cfg and set new.

@ENDNODE
